article.story: OGDEN, Utah -- — Bent Leuchten scored 29 points as UC Irvine beat Weber State 93-87 on Friday night. Leuchten added 11 rebounds and three blocks for the Anteaters (5-0). Justin Hohn scored 21 points and added six assists. Devin Tillis finished 6 of 6 from the field to finish with 15 points, while adding 11 rebounds. Blaise Threatt led the Wildcats (1-4) in scoring, finishing with 22 points, six assists and three steals. Dyson Koehler added 17 points for Weber State. Vasilije Vucinic had 12 points and two steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
